dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of black and white images that contain three shapes: triangle, square, and pentagon. Each image is 64x64 pixels in size and divided into three columns, with each column having a 0.5 probability of containing the corresponding shape.
dcterms:title: SIMPLE SHAPES

dcterms:creator: M. Afifi
dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of high-quality images of human hands from 190 subjects of various ages, photographed while opening and closing fingers against a uniform white background.
dcterms:title: HANDS

dcterms:creator: Y. LeCun
L. Bottou
Y. Bengio
P. Haffner
dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of 60,000 grayscale images of handwritten digits, commonly used for training various image processing systems.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset characterized by a mixture of 1D Gaussians used to study hallucinations in diffusion models.
dcterms:title: 1D GAUSSIAN

dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset characterized by a mixture of 2D Gaussians used to study hallucinations in diffusion models.
dcterms:title: 2D GAUSSIAN

dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset consisting of a mixture of 25 Gaussians arranged in a two-dimensional square grid used to study hallucinations in diffusion models.
dcterms:title: 2D Grid of Gaussians
